duck: Best practice - A best practice is a method or technique that has consistently shown results superior to those achieved with other means, and that is used as a benchmark.
The Practice, a TV program about a legal practice
Spiritual practice - A spiritual practice or spiritual discipline is the regular or full-time performance of actions and activities undertaken for the purpose of cultivating spiritual development.
Practice (learning method), a method of learning by repetition
Standards and Practices, a conventional, traditional, or otherwise standardised method
Phantom practice, phenomenon in which a person's abilities continue to improve, even without practising
Practice (social theory), a theoretical term for human action in society
Target practice, any exercise in which projectiles are fired at a specified target
Practice-based professional learning - Practice-based professional learning (pbpl) is best understood in contrast to 'classroom-' or 'theory-based' learning.
Medical practice, a company which engages in the practise of medicine

Practice of law - In its most general sense, the practice of law involves giving legal advice to clients, drafting legal documents for clients, and representing clients in legal negotiations and court proceedings...
